Citation.sTitle: The Conductivity of Imidazolium-Based Ionic Liquids from (-35 to 195) deg C. A. Variation of Cation s Alkyl Chain
Citation.sAbstract: Data for the conductivity (?) of the ionic liquids [emim][BF4], [bmim][BF4], [hmim][BF4], and [omim][BF4] from (-35 to 195) deg C are reported. The data can be well-fit with the Vogel-Fulcher-Tammann equation. Additionally, molar conductivities (?) were determined for the limited temperature range of (5 to 65) deg C. Walden plots of these data indicate that the investigated compounds can be classified as high-ionicity ionic liquids. It is suspected that the large difference between the present ? values and some of the literature values is mainly due to the neglect of BF4- hydrolysis.
